# A shadowing decl (y := y + 2) in an inner block of a lambda-bearing fn.
#
# Semantics (Go/Odin lexical scope + value semantics): the new `y`'s scope
# begins AFTER its initializer, so the RHS `y` reads the ENCLOSING y (= 1),
# binding a fresh independent value (= 3). The outer y is unchanged, so the
# final f(y) sees 1 -> 2. Expected: "inner 3inner2 30outer 2".
# Codegen reads the outer binding via a temp declared before the new C local
# (a naive `T h_y = (h_y + 2)` would read the inner one uninitialized -- UB).
#
# Also guards: lift_stmt's SDecl must compute the decl's type BEFORE pushing
# the name (sacc_stmt order) — pushing first crashed the compiler with
# "index 2 out of bounds" (names/types out of lockstep).
fn main():
    f := fn(x: int) -> int: x + 1
    y := 1
    if y > 0:
        y := y + 2
        print("inner " + str(y))
        g := fn(t: int) -> int: t * 10
        print("inner2 " + str(g(y)))
    print("outer " + str(f(y)))
